data.title: Venus on the Half Shell by Kilgore Trout
data.meta_description: Le privé du cosmos. Traduit de l'américain par Iawa Tate (Venus on the half-shell). Roman by TROUT (Kilgore) and a great selection of related books, art and collectibles available now at AbeBooks.com.
data.text:
Condition: Good. SHIPS FROM USA. Used books have different signs of use and do not include supplemental materials such as CDs, Dvds, Access Codes, charts or any other extra material. All used books might have various degrees of writing, highliting and wear and tear and possibly be an ex-library with the usual stickers and stamps. Dust Jackets are not guaranteed and when still present, they will have various degrees of tear and damage. All images are Stock Photos, not of the actual item. book.

Soft cover. Condition: Very Good +. Sixth Printing. Follow Simon Wagstaff through these 204 UNillustrated pages. Can we call this tale of Space Wanderer, a cult classic ?? Read more about : Queen Margaret, Shaltoonians, Goobnatz, Anubis, Chinese poets, apex-hole, bone spokes, skywriting, and lightless shapeless seas. Cond : Paper wrapper is blue green with red lettering. Is that Simon and Chworktap on the cover ? Standing inside a giant pecten shell ?? Colours bright, binding tight. Light edge wear. Name of p/o verso front cover. Collectible ! ! Quote (p. 55) : " They had ordered a couple of beers and Pussyloo plunged into her explanation, She said she'd be glad to tell him all she could in half an hour, but she'd have to talk a lot to get everything into ._._._. ." Size: 12mo.

Condition: Very Good. Book is in Used-VeryGood condition. Pages and cover are clean and intact. Used items may not include supplementary materials such as CDs or access codes. May show signs of minor shelf wear and contain very limited notes and highlighting. 0.2.

Digest Magazine. Condition: Very Good. Dust Jacket Condition: None. First appearance of this story in The Magazine Of Fantasy And Science Fiction, 2 part serial, Dec. 1974 and Jan. 1975, both issues vg, one reading crease near spine edge on front cover of Dec issue, one crease along spine on the Jan issue., both issues intact with full spines, nice looking.

Mass Market Paperback. Condition: Very Good. First Edition. First edition in book format. This is a paperback. Previously serialized in The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction. Wraps very good with light to moderate wear including creasing and edge wear. Spine is uncreased. Binding sound. Small numerical notation penned to inside front cover, and a previous owner's namestamp. Pages lightly age-toned. Text unmarked.

Soft Cover. Condition: Very Good Plus. Dust Jacket Condition: No DJ. Second printing - March 1975. # 440-06149-095 on the spine. Lightly rubbed along edges and front of spine, stain (1/2 inch) on inside front cover, previous owner's initials in ink on title page, else pages clean and binding firm. Overall, very good plus. Size: 12mo - over 6¾" - 7¾" tall.

Paperback. Condition: Good. 10th printing. Text is clean and unmarked, pages are tight and intact. Covers are scuffed. Bottom of spine is beginning to come apart. Pictures available on request.

Paperback. Condition: Very Good. 7 x 4", pict wraps, 204pp + ads (incl. Kurt Vonnegut), covers lightly rubbed, extremities worn, one corner bent, contents toned but still a very nice copy of the FIRST EDITION. Philip Jose Farmer.

Soft cover. Condition: Very Good. No Jacket. Stated first printing, February 1975. Mass market. Dell #6149. 204 pages. Overall condition is very good. Very negligible edge wear. Cover is shiny. (Great cover!) The pages are uniformly browned. The only real issue is three small piercings near the bottom edge of the cover. The deepest goes to page 13. It's as though someone took a sharp object to it. Automatic upgrade to first class domestic postage. 12mo - over 6¾ - 7¾" tall. Book.
